2 Solution by contrary objection (
                        〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                     ) is when the objection is not solved, but another stronger objection is propounded to the adversary: So Christ answered them that would have the Oyntment sold and given to the poor, by opposing a stronger reason: The poor ye have alwaies with you, but me not.

A Blam or chiding (
                        〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                     ) is, when we blame the adversary for that he disputeth against Piety and Honesty, or against manifest sense and Experience.

